<section class="narrative">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="narrative-grid">
      <div class="narrative-left">
        <p class="narrative-label">The Problem</p>
        <h2 class="narrative-heading">
          AI agents are powerful.<br />
          But they're still just tools.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="narrative-right">
        <p>
          Devin writes code. Codex runs tasks. Multica tracks them on a board.
          But when the session ends, everything resets. No memory. No growth.
          No one watching when things break.
        </p>
        <p>
          You're still the glue. You assign. You review. You fix. You context-switch
          between six tabs to figure out what happened while you slept.
        </p>
        <p class="narrative-highlight">
          What if your agents weren't tools you used &mdash; but employees you managed?
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .narrative {
    padding: var(--section-gap) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-3);
  }

  .narrative-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 80px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .narrative-label {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .narrative-heading {
    font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .narrative-right p {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--gray-9);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .narrative-right p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .narrative-highlight {
    color: var(--gray-12) !important;
    font-weight: 550;
    font-size: 19px !important;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
    padding-left: 20px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .narrative-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 32px;
    }
  }
</style>
